about.summary: A small collection of interesting and educational machine learning data sets which are used as examples in the 'mlr3' book (<https://mlr3book.mlr-org.com>), the use case gallery (<https://mlr3gallery.mlr-org.com>), or in other examples. All data sets are properly preprocessed and ready to be analyzed by most machine learning algorithms.  Data sets are automatically added to the dictionary of tasks if 'mlr3' is loaded.

name: r-mlr3data
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.6.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mlr3data
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/mlr3data_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/mlr3data/mlr3data_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ec23e09d12bfecd29ec228e76c0d6b2e8836184ebb098e01b0795261abd46ad9

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('mlr3data')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('mlr3data')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/mlr-org/mlr3data
  license: LGPL-3.0-only
  summary: A small collection of interesting and educational machine learning data sets which are used as examples in the 'mlr3' book (<https://mlr3book.mlr-org.com>), the use case gallery (<https://mlr3gallery.mlr-org.com>), or in other examples. All data sets are properly preprocessed and ready to be analyzed by most machine
    learning algorithms.  Data sets are automatically added to the dictionary of tasks if 'mlr3' is loaded.
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/LGPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - pascal-git
